        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "feat(provider): add OpenComputer sandbox provider",
        "body": "## What\n\nAdds `provider: opencomputer` (aliases `oc`, `open-computer`): a delegated-run provider backed by the [OpenComputer](https://app.opencomputer.dev) `oc` CLI (full Linux VMs). It follows the existing delegated-run pattern (`tensorlake`/`islo`/`modal`): Crabbox drives `oc sandbox create/get/list/kill` and `oc exec --wait` for lifecycle and command execution, while owning local config, repo claims, sync manifests/guardrails, slugs, timing summaries, and normalized list/status rendering.\n\n## Design notes\n\n- **Auth never touches Crabbox.** The OpenComputer API key lives in the `oc` CLI config (`oc config set api-key`); Crabbox stores/passes no `osb_` key in config or argv.\n- **No env forwarding (by design).** `oc exec --wait` is a buffered request that cannot carry values off the command line, and the streaming exec mode does not reliably propagate exit codes — so there is no safe non-argv channel for forwarded env. `--allow-env`/`--env-from-profile` are **rejected before any sandbox is created**, so secrets never reach an `oc` invocation.\n- **Archive sync without SSH/file-copy.** A `git ls-files`-driven gzipped tar is base64-encoded and appended to a remote staging file in chunks via `oc exec --wait`, then decoded + extracted in-sandbox. The provider advertises `FeatureArchiveSync`, so `--force-sync-large` and `--sync-only` are honored; `--checksum` is rejected.\n\n## Direct-API / SDK transport — considered, not adopted\n\nPer the maintainer suggestion to mirror wandb's API-client approach: there is **no official Go SDK** for OpenComputer (only TypeScript `@opencomputer/sdk` and Python `opencomputer-sdk`), and the `/api` REST surface (`X-API-Key`, `/exec/run`, `{path,content}`) is undocumented for Go. The supported, simple, e2e-proven `oc` CLI path is retained; a future REST transport could re-enable safe (off-argv) env forwarding.\n\n## Review fixes (ClawSweeper PR #236)\n\n- **[P1] secrets in argv** → env forwarding removed entirely; `--allow-env` now rejected up front. `env.go` / `writeRemoteFile` deleted.\n- **[P2] `--force-sync-large` unusable** → spec now advertises `FeatureArchiveSync`; `--sync-only` supported; redundant in-backend reject dropped in favor of core's spec-aware gate; added focused coverage.\n\n## Verification\n\n`gofmt`, `go vet`, `go test -race`, `scripts/check-docs.sh` clean; core coverage gate 91% ≥ 90%.\n\n**End-to-end against `app.opencomputer.dev` (redacted live output):**\n\n~~~text\n########## 1) DEFAULT SYNC RUN (archive over oc exec) ##########\nleased ocbx_sb-f1ca9f48 slug=brisk-shrimp provider=opencomputer sandbox=sb-f1ca9f48 ...\nsync candidate: 2 files, 25 B\nsync complete in 4.517s\nsync-marker-OK\nnested-OK\nopencomputer run summary sync=4.517s command=1.059s total=26.638s exit=0\n\n########## 2) SYNC-ONLY (sync, no command) ##########\nleased ocbx_sb-8898bba4 slug=pearl-shrimp provider=opencomputer sandbox=sb-8898bba4 ...\nsync complete in 4.604s\nsynced /workspace/crabbox\n\n########## 3) ENV FORWARDING REJECTED (SECRET_TOKEN set; nothing created) ##########\nprovider=opencomputer does not support forwarding environment variables: oc exec\ncannot carry values off the command line, so secrets would land in argv. ...\n# running sandboxes after rejection: []   (rejected before create; secret never reaches oc)\n~~~\n\n🤖 Generated with [Claude Code](https://claude.com/claude-code)",
